sentences: Cristina D'Avena (born 6 July 1964) is an Italian singer, actress, and TV personality.
In the early 1980s, she sang numerous cartoon theme songs, which were compiled into several successful albums.
In 1986, she appeared in Love me Licia, an Italian adaption of the Japanese manga Ai Shite Knight.
D'Avena has been performing concerts in Italy since the late 1990s.
In 2010, D'Avena returned to recording and releasing music.
In December 2009, D'Avena released her Magia di Natale album, which includes 12 traditional Christmas songs, all arranged by Valeriano Chiaravalle.

Cristina has been the presenter and the special guest of many TV programs for children, such as Holyday on Ice, Sabato al Circo, Luna Party, L' Allegria fa '90, Bim Bum Bam, Buona Domenica, I Fatti Vostri, Lo Zecchino
After co-hosting the TV program Matricole e Meteore for Canale 5, from 2012 to 2013 D'Avena hosted two music-themed programs on the TV channel Super!.
In 2014, she was the voice of Beatrice in the Italian dub of Over the Garden Wall.
She was a special guest in the 2016 edition of the Festival of Sanremo and was cast for the comedy TV program Colorado.
On 16 February 2018, D'Avena returned to television as a member of the jury on the first edition of Sanremo Giovani, a teenage talent show hosted by Antonella Clerici.
